Interview Questions
What is React?

React is a JavaScript library used to build reusable UI components and single-page applications.

What is JSX?

JSX stands for JavaScript XML. It allows writing HTML-like syntax inside JavaScript.

What is a Component?

A Component is a reusable piece of UI in React.

Why React is Fast?

React uses a Virtual DOM to update only the changed parts of the UI.

Difference between React and JavaScript?

JavaScript is a programming language, while React is a library built using JavaScript for creating user interfaces.
